snippet: The police chief said the dead included a senior prison warden, fitting a pattern of earlier attacks on security personnel.
abstract: Kenyan police official says gunmen killed five people and seriously wounded three at restaurant in Garissa, and that gunmen were supporters of Somalia's Shabab rebels.
lead_paragraph: The police chief said the dead included a senior prison warden, fitting a pattern of earlier attacks on security personnel.

headline.main: Kenya: Attack Kills 5; Shabab Backers Are Suspected
headline.print_headline: Kenya: Attack Kills 5; Shabab Backers Are Suspected
